column2: it is an old building but swanky food! Great home style fries
column3: breakfast tacos and coffee.  The chicken fried steak A-OK! just love the small felling of a community.  Food is always hot and tasty.  Cannot fit more than 35 for breakfast but there was never a line and sits were always full and people came in right on time.  If you feel awkward sitting to close to strangers while eating your meal
column4: this place is not for you.  Do visit one of their other locations. My other favorite is at the Museum District. Check their hours first.
